{
  "_comment": "Installed third-party modules whose objects are zero-inbound INSIDE the solution but are still live — they are invoked externally (OData / fmurlscript / a companion app) or managed by the module itself. trace.py 'dead' lists any unreferenced match under a separate MODULE category instead of flagging it dead, so a module's objects are never mistaken for your solution's dead code.",
  "_usage": "These are SHIPPED DEFAULTS. To add your own modules (e.g. InspectorPro, OttoFMS, a fmurlscript integration), copy this file to 'modules.json' (same folder) and add entries there — your file is merged over these defaults by 'label', so you do not need to re-declare agentic-fm. Matching is by object NAME first (folder-independent, so reorganising the Script Workspace folders does not break it); 'folder_contains' is only a secondary hint. A match on ANY of name_prefixes / name_exact / folder_contains tags the object.",
  "_example_entry": {
    "label": "InspectorPro",
    "name_prefixes": ["INSP"],
    "name_exact": ["[Settings] InspectorPro"],
    "folder_contains": ["InspectorPro", "INSP"]
  },
  "modules": [
    {
      "label": "agentic-fm",
      "name_prefixes": ["AGFM", "Agentic-fm"],
      "name_exact": ["Explode XML", "Push Context", "Get agentic-fm path"],
      "folder_contains": ["agentic-fm"]
    }
  ]
}
